# Use `Promise.allSettled` instead of `Promise.all`

Never use `Promise.all` for concurrent async operations. Always use `Promise.allSettled` so that one failure does not abort the others.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — one rejection cancels all
const [a, b] = await Promise.all([fetchA(), fetchB()])

// ✅ GOOD — each settles independently
const [ra, rb] = await Promise.allSettled([fetchA(), fetchB()])
const a = ra.status === "fulfilled" ? ra.value : fallback
const b = rb.status === "fulfilled" ? rb.value : fallback
```
